<div class="row">
  <h1>What the FAQs</h1>
  <br/>
  <ul>
    <li><b>What does the ArtJump grant include?</b><br/>
    <p>The 2020 ArtJump grants are designed to specifically cover a fixed amount of transportation costs for existing arworks.The grants will go towards artists that will take their art on tour through (their selection of happenings) in Europe.</p>
    <p>Each artist will bring their work to Where the Sheep Sleep 2020 and at least one other event in Europe. These events can be Burns, Burning Man inspired events, Maker Faires or other artistic endeavours.    </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Who can apply?</b><br/>
      <p>Any artist (including performers) can apply with an existing artwork.
      </p></li>
    <li>
    <b>How many grants will be awarded in 2020?</b><br/>
    <p>This year we plan to fund a minimum of 2 and maximum of 6 existing art projects.
    </p></li>
    <li>
    <b>What does it grant?</b><br/>
      <p>This year the total budget of €6,000 (Euros) is available for applicants.
        You can apply for a transportation grant to a maximum of €3,000. </p>
    <p>Note to artists: Ask only for what you need. The jury will take into account how your transport budget is related to your overall project and budget. A realistic budget will positively affect your chances of receiving a grant.
    </p></li>

    <li><b>Who’s the jury?</b><br/>
    <p>The international jury - who all have their hearts and feet deep in Burning Man communities - will have the honour to make the grant selection
    </p>
      <p>Last years jury:</p>
      <ul class="bullet-list">
        <li>Bart Grob, chairman of the jury</li>
        <li>Hampus Lindblad, Borderland</li>
        <li>Ifat Golan, Art team and board member Midburn</li>
        <li>Marijntje Schook, Dutch artist</li>
        <li>Misa Rygrova, Meta Regional Committee Burningman</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <br/>
    <li>
      <b>What will the jury be looking for?</b><br/>
      <p>The jury committee will judge your application on the following parameters:</p>
      <p>
    Parameters for art participation:</p>
      <ul class="bullet-list">
        <li>It MUST be an existing art piece (including performances).</li>
        <li>The art must already be in Europe.</li>
        <li>The art must be participatory. We are defining participatory as at least a few of the following:
       <ul class="bullet-list">
          <li>Art that is interactive.
          <li>Art that prompts the viewer to act.
          <li>Art that can be experienced in more ways than visually.
          <li>Art that prompts people to interact with one another.
          <li>Art that responds to participants and its environment.
          <li>Art that causes people to reflect on the larger community.
          <li>Art that challenges the viewers’ traditional perspective on art.
          <li>Art that belongs to the public and exists for the benefit of all.
        </ul></li>
        <li>The artist will bring their work to Where the Sheep Sleep and at least one other event in Europe. These events can be burns, burning man inspired events, maker fairs or a public space.</li>
        <li>You must have a practical transportation plan to and from the event(s). Remember, these are leave-no-trace events.</li>
        <li>Shipping, events tickets, any insurance and any other art-related logistics are the artists’ own responsibilities.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To receive the art grant, the artist must define which events or public space (up to 3 within one year/2020) you would like to bring your art to.
      </p>
      <p>
    You must have a practical transportation plan to and from the events (Upon registering you can download a template). Remember, these are leave-no-trace events. Shipping, events tickets, any insurance and any other art-related logistics are the artists’ own responsibilities. ArtJump grants only cover transportation costs.
      </p>

    <li><b>How to apply?</b><br/>
    <p>To apply for a grant, you must submit pictures and a written description of your interactive or participatory art, as well as a description of your transportation plan to and from the events.
      Please note: you are responsible for securing your own entrance ticket to each event you plan on attending with your art. Register <a href="http://artjump.burningman.nl/users/sign_up">here</a> to create a user account and then create your proposal <a href="http://artjump.burningman.nl/dreams/new">here</a>.</p>
      <p>
    Please submit up to three pictures of your art once the proposal is created by editing your proposal on your personal page by clicking the 'Manage Images' button.
      </p></li>
    <li>
    <b>What’s the deadline for registering?</b><br/>
    <p>Applications are due March 31st, 2020 at 11:00 (GMT+1).
    </p>

    <p>Grant applicants will be contacted by email.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>What is the jury process?</b><br/>
    <p>After 31st March, when all applications are in, the jury will have a chance to review the projects. Based on the parameters mentioned above, the jury will score each application. In addition to the artistic parameters, the projects are also scored on feasibility.
    </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
